## 1. Introduction  
The Playlist Manager is a Python-based console application designed to help users maintain a personal music playlist. It provides essential CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations in a simple and intuitive menu-driven interface.

## 2. Objectives  
- To implement file handling using CSV  
- To create a persistent data storage system  
- To develop a user-friendly menu-driven program  
- To practice error handling and input validation  
- To build a practical utility tool using only built-in Python modules  

## 3. Features  
| Feature                  | Description                                      |
|--------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Add Song                 | Adds a new song (prevents duplicates)            |
| Remove Song              | Removes exact song name                          |
| View Playlist            | Displays numbered list of all songs              |
| Search Song              | Partial & case-insensitive search                |
| Clear Playlist           | Deletes all songs after confirmation            |
| Auto Save/Load           | Uses playlist.csv for persistence                |

## 4. Technology Used  
- **Language:** Python 3.x  
- **Modules:** csv (built-in)  
- **File Format:** CSV (human-readable & editable)  
- **IDE/Editor:** Any (VS Code, PyCharm, IDLE, etc.)  

## 5. System Requirements  
- Python 3.8 or above  
- Operating System: Windows / macOS / Linux  
- Storage: < 10 KB  

## 6. How to Execute  
1. Save the code as `playlist_manager.py`  
2. Open terminal/command prompt  
3. Run: `python playlist_manager.py`  
